#
# Everything this build touches is a reproducible product of sources.lock + the NDK pin, so
# none of it is committed. What IS committed is the recipe: sources.lock, the scripts, and
# the README.
#
# In particular the built libmpv.so is NOT committed. Per ABI it is tens of megabytes of
# third-party LGPL binary; committing it would bloat every clone, put binaries under REUSE
# annotations that inline SPDX headers cannot reach, and — worst — decouple the shipped
# binary from the pins that are supposed to describe it. Gradle consumes dist/ (or a
# release artifact) instead; see README "Where the output goes".

downloads/
src/
dist/
# The repository-root .gitignore already ignores build/ everywhere; repeated here so this
# directory is self-describing.
build/
